        <body>
            <ab type="factoid" subtype="nameVariant" xml:id="factoid-11" resp="#dschwartz">
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/spear/821-11</idno>
                <listPerson>
                    <person>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862"> Malkha the Mendicant and Stranger </persName>
                    </person>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/821"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">360</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">562</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </ab>
            <ab type="factoid" subtype="nameVariant" xml:id="factoid-1" resp="#syoung">
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/spear/821-1</idno>
                <listPerson>
                    <person>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">a certain stranger</persName>
                    </person>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/821"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">361</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">563</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </ab>
            <ab type="factoid" subtype="event" xml:id="factoid-2" resp="#syoung">
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/spear/821-2</idno>
                <listEvent>
                    <event
                        ana="http://syriaca.org/keyword/monks http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasticism http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasteries http://syriaca.org/keyword/poverty http://syriaca.org/keyword/vespers http://syriaca.org/keyword/prayer">
                        <desc><date notBefore="0530" notAfter="0536" calendar="Gregorian">Sometime
                                between 530 and 536, in the month of November</date>,<persName
                                ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">a stranger</persName>came to
                                the<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/399">convent outside
                                    of<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/8"
                                >Amida</placeName></placeName>. Dirty and worn out,<persName
                                ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">he</persName>stood at vespers
                            and at table without speaking. </desc>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/821"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">361</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">563</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </ab>
            <ab type="factoid" subtype="nameVariant" xml:id="factoid-3" resp="#syoung">
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/spear/821-3</idno>
                <listPerson>
                    <person>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1560">Adam</persName>
                    </person>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/821"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">362</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">564</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </ab>
            <ab type="factoid" subtype="event" xml:id="factoid-4" resp="#syoung">
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/spear/821-4</idno>
                <listEvent>
                    <event
                        ana="http://syriaca.org/keyword/humility http://syriaca.org/keyword/prayer http://syriaca.org/keyword/silence http://syriaca.org/keyword/sin http://syriaca.org/keyword/emotions">
                        <desc> 
                            In <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/399">the convent</placeName>,
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">the man</persName> refused to speak to the brothers, calling himself
                            a stranger, sinner, and son of <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1560">Adam</persName>. </desc>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/821"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">362</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">564</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </ab>
            <ab type="factoid" subtype="event" xml:id="factoid-5" resp="#syoung">
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/spear/821-5</idno>
                <listEvent>
                    <event
                        ana="http://syriaca.org/keyword/sleep http://syriaca.org/keyword/humility http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasteries http://syriaca.org/keyword/silence http://syriaca.org/keyword/tears http://syriaca.org/keyword/emotions">
                        <desc> While in <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/399">the
                                convent</placeName><persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862"
                                >the man</persName>refused to sleep during the night while others
                            were awake, and during service he would lie on the floor crying,
                                leading<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3183">the
                                archimandrite</persName>question him. </desc>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/821"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">363</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">565</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </ab>
            <ab type="factoid" subtype="nameVariant" xml:id="factoid-6" resp="#syoung">
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/spear/821-6</idno>
                <listPerson>
                    <person>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3183">the archimandrite</persName>
                    </person>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/821"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">363</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">565</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </ab>
            <ab type="factoid" subtype="event" xml:id="factoid-7" resp="#syoung">
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/spear/821-7</idno>
                <listEvent>
                    <event
                        ana="http://syriaca.org/keyword/tears http://syriaca.org/keyword/humility http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasteries http://syriaca.org/keyword/monks http://syriaca.org/keyword/monastic-heads http://syriaca.org/keyword/vespers">
                        <desc><persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3183">The
                                archimandrite</persName>approached<persName
                                ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">the man</persName>about his
                            actions. Attending vespers, he began to cry
                            because of his humility and sinfulness before God. </desc>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/821"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">364</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">567</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </ab>
            <ab type="factoid" subtype="event" xml:id="factoid-8" resp="#syoung">
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/spear/821-8</idno>
                <listEvent>
                    <event
                        ana="http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasticism http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasteries http://syriaca.org/keyword/monks http://syriaca.org/keyword/silence http://syriaca.org/keyword/tears http://syriaca.org/keyword/humility http://syriaca.org/keyword/emotions">
                        <desc> Speaking with<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3183">the
                                archimandrite</persName>,<persName
                                ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">the man</persName>decided to
                            stay in<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/399">the
                                convent</placeName>for the winter. He continued in his
                            silence and weeping, garnering the appreciation of the brothers, who
                            were encouraged by him. </desc>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/821"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">369</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">571</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </ab>
            <ab type="factoid" subtype="event" xml:id="factoid-9" resp="#syoung">
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/spear/821-9</idno>
                <listEvent>
                    <event
                        ana="http://syriaca.org/keyword/prayer http://syriaca.org/keyword/memory http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasticism http://syriaca.org/keyword/monks http://syriaca.org/keyword/humility http://syriaca.org/keyword/silence http://syriaca.org/keyword/tears http://syriaca.org/keyword/emotions http://syriaca.org/keyword/prophecy">
                        <desc> In his tears and sighs,<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862"
                                >the blessed man</persName>prophecied that he would die in three
                            days. While on his deathbed, he shared with the
                            brothers that he had been thirty-nine years since he had taken his
                            monastic vows, asking for their prayers and blessings. </desc>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/821"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">371</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">573</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </ab>
            <ab type="factoid" subtype="event" xml:id="factoid-10" resp="#syoung">
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/spear/821-10</idno>
                <listEvent>
                    <event
                        ana="http://syriaca.org/keyword/death http://syriaca.org/keyword/monks http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasticism http://syriaca.org/keyword/prayer http://syriaca.org/keyword/sleep">
                        <desc> Close to death,<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">the
                                blessed man</persName>went into the vestry to pray. After a
                                while,<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3183">the
                                archimandrite</persName>entered to find<persName
                                ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">the man</persName>praying on
                            his mat, as if he was asleep. As <persName
                                ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3183"> the
                                Archimandrite</persName>spoke,<persName
                                ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1862">the man</persName>gave up his
                            soul to God. </desc>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/821"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">372</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="p">574</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </ab>
        </body>
